  "texts": [
    "because these algorithms are opaque and varied, we treat everything about how the LLM goes from its training data to a particular text response as a black box.",
    "The framework distinguishes between two types of empirical applications -prediction and estimation -and provides four main results.",
    "Our first result relates to prediction problems, in which the researcher predicts a linked economic variable using the associated text.",
    "For example, in asset pricing, we might want to know how well stock prices can be predicted using news headlines.",
    "We show that for LLM outputs to be validly used in prediction problems, the LLM must satisfy a single condition we refer to as \"no training leakage.\""
  ]
}